==English==

===Adjective===

# personal attribute - averse to cold air, or cold water - more averse than normal.

===Examples / Explanation===
person averse to going out in cold weather, someone who puts on warm clothing at the slightest hint of a coolish breeze, someone who is averse to going swimming because the water is less than ideally warm.

===Locality===
This word seems to be specific to an area around Stafford, in the North West Midlands of England.